Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone scored 124 not out from 85 deliveries in a 140-run partnership with Sam Curran
England finished its successful run chase on 329-5 with 15 balls remaining
Phil Salt scored 59 and Jacob Bethell scored a maiden half century
John Turner dismissed Brandon King (7) and Evin Lewis (4) inside four overs
Keacy Carty and Shai Hope put on 143 runs for the third wicket
Sherfane Rutherford scored 54 and Shimron Hetmeyer scored 24 in the West Indies innings
Post-Match Reflections: Liam Livingstone expressed pride in leading England to the second-highest successful ODI chase in the West Indies
John Turner's early wickets put West Indies in trouble
Miscellaneous Highlights: West Indies captain Shai Hope made 117 in the first innings
Phil Salt and Jacob Bethell gave England a solid start
West Indies struggled with cramps in warm conditions
